Berkelium

Symbol:   Bk
Relative atomic mass: [247]
Atomic number: 97
Group numbers: 3
Period: 7
Standard state (20 ^oC): solid

Discovery: 1949 Stanley G. Thompson, Albert Ghiorso, Glenn T. Seaborg (US)

Berkelium was discovered by Stanley G. Thompson, Albert Ghiorso, and Glenn T.
Seaborg (US) in 1949. Named after 'Berkeley', a city in California, home of the
University of California, USA. It is synthetic radioactive metal. Berkelium was
made by bombarding americium with alpha particles.

Electronic configuration: [Rn] 5f^9 7s^2
Formal oxidation number: +3 +4
Atomic radius: 170 pm

Electronegativities: -
Thermal conductivity: - W/(m K)
Electrical resistivity (20 ^oC): - microOhm cm

Melting point: 1050 ^oC
Boiling point: - ^oC

Heat of fusion: - kJ/mol
Heat of vaporization: - kJ/mol
Heat of atomization: 291 kJ/mol

